INVESTIGATIONS are under way after  a teenager was assaulted in Glasgow city centre  in the early hours. Probe under way after teenager assaulted INVESTIGATIONS are under way after  a teenager was assaulted in Glasgow city centre  in the early hours.Police were in attendance in Bath Street where a section was closed off.A police spokeswoman said officers were called to a report of an assault in Bath Street shortly after 2am.She said officers were continuing their inquiries.The victim, thought to be 18-years-old, was taken by ambulance to Glasgow Royal Infirmary for treatment. 